Announced in 2013 and first run last year, Formula 4 is an open-wheeled motor racing competition designed for junior drivers as a stepping stone to Formula One. Vehicles may have a maximum power output of 160hp and must cost less than €9,500.

There is no global championship, but individual nations can host their own championships according to rules and specifications of the Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile.

Michael Schumacher suffered severe head injuries in a skiing accident in Meribel in the French Alps in December 2013. He emerged from an induced coma in June last year, and left hospital in September.

He has since started to recognise family members, according to someone claiming to be a family friend.

Philippe Streiff, a former Formula One driver, told French media Schumacher 'has yet to recover the power of speech' but is 'nevertheless starting to recognise those close to him'. 

